BioConsortia, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 9:19 PM ET
Biotechnology

Company Overview of BioConsortia, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
BioConsortia, Inc., an agricultural biotechnology company, discovers, develops, and commercializes microbial consortia seed treatment and soil additive products for improving agricultural yield. The company uses a proprietary method for the selection of beneficial microbial consortia for crop improvement. The company’s products and research projects include products for enhanced fertilizer utilization and substitution of N, P, K, and S; plant growth improvement of harvestable yield, root mass, and accelerated development products; and other desirable crop traits, such as abiotic tolerance, biotic resistance, and enhanced metabolite expression. It designs its microbial consortia to be applied...
BioConsortia, Inc., an agricultural biotechnology company, discovers, develops, and commercializes microbial consortia seed treatment and soil additive products for improving agricultural yield. The company uses a proprietary method for the selection of beneficial microbial consortia for crop improvement. The company’s products and research projects include products for enhanced fertilizer utilization and substitution of N, P, K, and S; plant growth improvement of harvestable yield, root mass, and accelerated development products; and other desirable crop traits, such as abiotic tolerance, biotic resistance, and enhanced metabolite expression. It designs its microbial consortia to be applied as seed treatments and soil additives. BioConsortia, Inc. was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Davis, California. The company has R&D facilities in New Zealand and the United States.
Detailed Description


P.O. Box 675Davis, CA 96517United StatesFounded in 2014



Phone: 530-601-6626

bioconsortia.com







